title: Boomerang
description: Cisco and Poncho are being impersonated by two bandits who have committed robbery and murder, so they have to break jail to prove their innocence.

title: Counterfeit Money
description: Cisco and Pancho are asked by Marshal Ben Lane to track down a gang of counterfeiters in Durado. Cisco suspects the local banker and his clerk to be involved in the counterfeit, but cannot prove anything. He sets some traps for the gang. One of the traps involves arresting Pancho as an alleged bank robber.

title: Rustling
description: Joe Dawson, foreman at a ranch in San Saba, asks his old friend Cisco to come and help them catch a gang of cattle rustlers. When the leader of the gang hears of this, he orders two of his henchmen to kill Joe and blame the murder on Cisco. Cisco and Pancho have to keep away from the sheriff at the same as they are searching for the gang and the missing cattle.

title: Big Switch
description: The Sheriff in Bonanza orders his assistant to bring the murderer Jim Hardy to the state prison, where Hardy is going to be hanged. On the way the assistant is killed by a shot from a man, who releases Hardy and brings him to his boss, Jim Holbrook. Holbrook plans to kill his employer, the ranch owner Henry P. Murdock, and replace him with Hardy, who resembles Murdock. Through this switch, Holbrook will get control over the ranch himself. The sheriff thinks that it is Cisco who has killed his assistant. Cisco and Pancho have to solve the whole mystery to prove that they are innocent.

title: Convict Story
description: Cisco is convinced by a beautiful woman that her brother, who escaped from prison, is trying to prove he was framed for a murder did not commit.

title: Oil Land
description: When a rancher discovers oil on his property, he is shot dead by one of his greedy workers, and Cisco and Poncho are accused of the murder.

title: Chain Lightning
description: A super fast on the draw, ex-con gets out of prison, and is bent on killing Cisco and Bill Shannon for sending him there.

title: Medicine Flats
description: Cisco and Pancho work with a sheriff and beautiful undercover female agent for the cattlemen's association, to break up a cattle rustling operation.

title: Railroad Land Rush
description: Cisco and Pancho come across the disrobed body of a railway inspector sent to a town to investigate shady real estate dealings in the name of the railway.

title: The Will
description: Cisco and Pancho come across Bob Drake being chased by two outlaws. After helping him, Cisco hears his story of being framed for a gold robbery. Cisco believes Bob and decides to investigate.

title: Cattle Quarantine
description: Cisco and Pancho stumble across a ranch where the owner is arguing with a number of farm hands. It appears some of the cows have died from disease, and the rest will need to be quarantined. Cisco always happy to help a pretty lady, decides to get to the bottom of the issue.

title: Renegade Son
description: Cisco and Pancho break a woman out of jail, after she has been sentenced to hang for a murder she did not commit.

title: False Marriage
description: Jasper King has asked his old friend Cisco to help him stop the marriage between his niece Nancy and the gangster Duke Ralston. Cisco and Pancho break the wedding ceremony and run away with the protesting bride. During a quarrel about this Duke kills Jasper. Nancy tells the sheriff that it is Cisco and Pancho who have killed her uncle. To prove their innocence Cisco and Pancho have to find the real murder and deliver him to the sheriff.

title: Wedding Blackmail
description: Cisco and Pancho try to help a young bank teller, whose marriage to the bank president's daughter is endangered by two gunmen who are blackmailing him about a secret from his past.

title: Lynching Story
description: When a bank president is murdered, the townspeople accuse the man's future son-in-law of the crime and a lynching party is formed. Cisco and Pancho must find out who the real killers are before the mob hangs the innocent man.

title: Newspaper Crusader
description: Cisco and Pancho arrive in the town of Sundance. The town is in turmoil with a local thug 'Judd' trying to take over. After Cisco sees the destruction of a local newspaper office, he decides to hang around and sort things out.

title: Dog Story
description: When a wounded dog tracks down the man who murdered his master, a gold mine owner, Cisco tries to get proof he is the killer.

title: Confession for Money
description: A young woman asks Cisco and Pancho to help her fianc√©e, who has confessed to a robbery and murder he didn't commit in order to get money for his mother's surgery.

title: The Old Bum
description: A poor man steals Cisco and Pancho's horses, trying to raise money to impress his visiting daughter. Later, he becomes the unsuspecting fall guy in a cattle rustling operation.

title: Haven for Heavies
description: Cisco follows the killer of a U.S. marshal to the town of Twin Buttes, which is notorious as a haven for criminals of all kinds.

title: Pancho Held Hostage
description: After having captured and jailed a bank robber, Pancho is then taken hostage by the robber's sister, who threatens to kill him unless Cisco frees her brother.

title: Freight Line Feud
description: Cisco and Pancho come upon Klondike, who was just robbed of his wagon and freight. Upon hearing the bad news, Elaine, the hot-headed owner of Western Freighting Co., takes a couple of shots at Bill Jarrett, owner of Jarrett Stage Line, which is soon to open. She thinks Jarrett, to whom she refuses to sell her company, Cisco and Pancho are in cahoots in order to force her out of business. She's not convinced otherwise, even after Cisco and Pancho find and return her now empty wagon. When Cisco hears of a test run that Jarrett is making the next day, he figures out a way to clear their names and catch the real crooks.

title: Phoney Sheriff
description: Cisco and Pancho are tricked by a cattle buyer, who used a fake sheriff and deputies to get them to turn over a friend's cattle. They set out after the swindler to get the cattle back.

title: Uncle Disinherits Niece
description: A rancher threatens to disinherit his niece unless she stops seeing her boyfriend. When the rancher is found murdered, suspicion falls on her lover. Cisco and Pancho must find the real killer and clear the young man's name.

title: Phoney Heiress
description: A young woman who has inherited some property is about to be swindled out of it by a crooked lawyer who has hired an impostor to pretend to be the rightful owner. She asks Cisco and Pancho to help her keep her property.

title: Water Rights
description: Cisco and Pancho witness some strange behavior by a coach driver near the town of Guunison. Suddenly they are accused of attempting to rob the stage, Cisco clearly wants to clear his name, however while investigating Cisco discovers a much bigger game being played.

title: Performance Bond
description: Cisco and Pancho try to find who has been sabotaging a woman's company freight wagons, before she looses the $20,000 performance bond she put up.

title: Stolen Bonds
description: Cisco and Pancho are after a thief who stole $25,000 in bonds from a friend of theirs. They soon begin to suspect that a young woman who is a cook in a hotel is actually the thief's partner.

title: Postal Inspector
description: While in the town of Baxter Center, Cisco and Pancho stop by to drop a letter in the mail. To their surprise, they find themselves being arrested on suspicion of being part of a gang of mail robbers.

title: Jewelry Store Fence
description: A crazy old man tries to kill Cisco and Pancho with a crossbow.

title: Foreign Agent
description: Cisco and Pancho have to stop a gang of foreign agents from getting their hands on a vast tungsten deposit.

title: Medicine Man Show
description: After answering Chief Flying Cloud's smoke signal for help in preventing an Indian war, Cisco and Pancho go undercover as Professor Lorenzo Lombardi and Chief Waho's Cure-All Medicine Show, in an attempt to break up an arms smuggling ring.

title: Ghost Story
description: A pair of silver smugglers murder their partner, a local rancher, when he tries to back out of the operation. Cisco and Pancho set out to get them.

title: Protective Association
description: Cisco and Pancho help a rancher and his daughter who are victims of a gang running a "protection" racket.

title: Kid Sister Trouble
description: Cisco an Pancho get mixed up with a sharpshooting lady gambler and a gang of counterfeiters.

title: Water Toll
description: Cisco and Pancho come to the aid of a lady rancher who's fighting a greedy cattle baron who's making ranchers and drovers pay him for watering their herds.

title: The Bates Story
description: Cisco and Pancho are forced to switch clothes with two escaped convicts, and are later arrested when they are mistaken for the fleeing criminals.

title: Water Well Oil
description: Cisco and Pancho find themselves being shot at by a quick-tempered young man who's found oil on his ranch and thinks that they're trying to take it from him.

title: Vigilante Story
description: In order to break up a gang of vigilantes that's terrorizing the people of Buffalo Flats, Cisco and Pancho head into town disguised as a gambler and an organ grinder.

roles.char: The Cisco Kid posing as Tex

title: Hidden Valley
description: Cisco and Poncho are trapped by a ex pirate who runs a slave camp, with Indian guards, in a secret valley with his gorgeous niece who wants no part of it.

title: Carrier Pigeon
description: Cisco and Pancho meet up with a woman who claims to be an insurance investigator tracking down a stolen diamond necklace.

title: Hypnotist Murder
description: Cisco and Pancho intervene when a woman tries to get her husband and his rich father killed, while later, she gets blackmailed by a another woman.

title: Romany Caravan
description: While at a gypsy camp, Cisco gets into an altercation over a woman and Pancho finds himself being on the receiving end of the unwelcome attentions of a large dancing bear.

title: Robber Crow
description: Cisco and Pancho find themselves in the middle of a feud between the guards at a gold mine and the mine's workers, whom the guards suspect of stealing gold from the mine.

title: Sleeping Gas
description: Cisco and Pancho go up against a gang of bank robbers who use a sleeping gas potion in their robberies.

title: Quarter Horse
description: Cisco takes part in an endurance race to help prove 4 quarter-horses can beat one thoroughbred, while the man entrusted to hold the race money, is planing to steal it.

title: Jewelry Holdup
description: Cisco and Pancho get involved when a gang of jewel thieves, who've mailed themselves part of their haul, are prevented from getting their package by a by-the-book postal clerk, and they then decide to take it by force.

title: Ghost Town
description: Cisco and Pancho find a woman near death in the desert and learn she is a target for murder because she is headed for a ghost town to prove an inheritance and upon accompanying her find an addled innkeeper and other characters.

title: Quicksilver Murder
description: A crooked prosecutor robs quicksilver shipments, then uses chemical weapons to commit murder. Cisco and Pancho investigate.

title: Buried Treasure
description: Cisco tries to save the cabin boy of famed pirate Jean Lafitte--now a wizened old man--from the hands of an ancient old crone and her evil sons, who are after Lafitte's lost treasure.

title: Spanish Dagger
description: Cisco rescues an old prospector from a mine explosion. He discovers an ancient jeweled dagger that places a curse on anyone who steals it.

title: Pancho and the Pachyderm
description: Cisco and Pancho meet up with Griffith's traveling show consisting of ex-sheriff Ben, his daughter Sally and their trained elephant Mildred. Stokes and Shaddon are after a medallion they have. When Ben is captured, Cisco goes after them but will need the help of Mildred to round them up.

roles.char: Professor John Farris aka Sam Chanfield

title: Church in the Town
description: A traveling Jehovah Witness minister and his son stop in the town where the minister's estranged brother lives. While there, they are persecuted by some of the local thugs.

title: Smuggled Silver
description: Cisco is asked by a dying boy on behalf of a old friend to investigate the theft and smuggling from Mexico of the friend's silver and suspects during the inquiry that a federal agent has been killed while he and Pancho become targets.

title: Freedom of the Press
description: Cisco and Pancho help a newspaper editor who's caught in the middle of an important election fight between a crooked mayor trying to hold on to power and a young reformer.

title: The Raccoon Story
description: Cisco and Pancho are asked to deliver the death certificate of Gus Brown, an old miner, to the town of Sweetwater. They discover that Brown has left all of his property to his best friend--his dog.

title: The Black Terror
description: In an attempt to round up two rival bands of outlaws, Cisco wears a black mask and goes undercover as The Black Terror.

title: Cisco Meets the Gorilla
description: A band of outlaws commits a series of robberies, while a sheriff and his deputy hunt down a gorilla on the loose.

title: Not Guilty
description: Pancho's nephew is the witness to a murder and identifies the killer, who is arrested. When the circuit judge arrives for the trial, he is actually one of the killer's friends, who is impersonating the real judge in an effort to free his buddy.

title: Rodeo
description: A confidence man solicits entry fees to a sham rodeo. Pancho is among the many would-be participants to be fooled by the scam.

title: Double Deal
description: In order to exact revenge against Cisco for having once put him in jail, a man commits a gold shipment holdup while disguised as the Cisco Kid.

title: Horseless Carriage
description: Pancho's nephew buys a new "horseless carriage", but finds himself in trouble when thieves use it as a getaway vehicle after they've robbed the bank.

title: The Ventriloquist
description: Pancho learns how to throw his voice. Meanwhile, Cisco deals with a crooked assayer.

title: Extradition Papers
description: Pancho breaks in a new pair of boots.

title: New Evidence
description: A local judge enlists Cisco and Pancho as Marshal and bailiff to capture and try a murder suspect.

title: Doorway to Nowhere
description: The bedroom of a house mysteriously disappears.

title: The Kidnapped Cameraman
description: A photographer takes a picture of a murder. The killer and his brother go after him.

title: The Tumblers
description: There's a new sheriff in town, and he happens to be a gymnast.

title: Arroyo Millionaire's Castle
description: Cisco and Poncho stumble on a gold theft, before they can do anything the local sheriff also arrives. He decides Cisco is the real thief and intends to put before the courts.

title: Witness
description: Pancho is shot after interrupting a holdup, but he finds time is on his side.

title: School Marm
description: A new school marm is kidnapped and held for ransom.

title: Quick on the Trigger
description: Cisco and Pancho contend with a sheriff who shoots first and asks questions later.

title: Six Gun Cupids
description: Cisco and Pancho help a young couple elope.

title: The Epidemic
description: A town sick with smallpox awaits its vaccine, but bandits rob the mail rider and hold it for ransom.

title: Mr. X
description: When a miner is trapped by a cave in, it's up to his pet monkey, Mr. X, to save the day.

title: He Couldn't Quit
description: Cisco and Pancho are destined to cross paths with a pretty palm reader.
